Steps.Message: Update at 18:25 - Thanks for your continued patience tonight. I know it can be worrying having a power cut as it heads further into the evening, and our staff are still working hard to get your power back on. Further specialist teams are now on site and working on repairs, and our estimated timeframe remains unchanged. I'll continue to keep you updated with our progress, but if you have any questions or concerns, our team are always here on 08003163105.

We became aware of this power cut at 14:51. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing
